article.headline: Durugordon scores 36 points and makes 16 straight free throws to lead Siena past Niagara 93-88
article.linkText: Durugordon scores 36 points and makes 16 straight free throws to lead Siena past Niagara 93-88
article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. -- — Sean Durugordon had 36 points and 12 rebounds and Siena scored 60 points in the second half to beat Niagara 93-88 on Monday, ending an eight-game losing streak. Durugordon broke the program's 61-year record for most made free throws (16) in a game without a miss. The previous mark was 15 by Frank Ryan on Dec. 4, 1963. Michael Eley scored 18 points while shooting 8 for 14, including 1 for 3 from beyond the arc, and added five rebounds for the Saints (3-13, 2/3 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Killian Gribben shot 4 of 6 from the field and 4 for 4 from the line to finish with 13 points. Ahmad Henderson II led the way for the Purple Eagles (7-9, 3-3) with 29 points and two steals. Luke Bumbalough added 15 points and seven assists for Niagara. In addition, Kwane Marble II finished with 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
